
Overview of noun melancholy

The noun melancholy has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (4) melancholy -- (a feeling of thoughtful sadness)
2. melancholy -- (a constitutional tendency to be gloomy and depressed)
3. black bile, melancholy -- (a humor that was once believed to be secreted by the kidneys or spleen and to cause sadness and melancholy)

Overview of adj melancholy

The adj melancholy has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) melancholy, melancholic -- (characterized by or causing or expressing sadness; "growing more melancholy every hour"; "her melancholic smile"; "we acquainted him with the melancholy truth")
2. somber, sombre, melancholy -- (grave or even gloomy in character; "solemn and mournful music"; "a suit of somber black"; "a somber mood")
